article.headline: SE Louisiana 73, Texas-Arlington 69
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Terry Bryant scored 19 points, tying a career high, to lead Southeastern Louisiana over Texas-Arlington on Saturday, 73-69. Quennell Green added 14 points and Ray Cummings a career-high 12 in a game that saw Southeastern rally from 12 points down to outscore the Mavericks 30-14 in the game's final 11:36. Southeastern (10-7, 2-2 Southland Conference) shot less than 42 percent for the game. But the Lions had only 10 turnovers -- half the number committed by Texas-Arlington -- and scored 28 points off turnovers. A 3-pointer by Green -- one of four he hit -- put the Lions up 61-59. The Mavericks went up briefly, but Green -- and another 3 -- put the Lions up for good with 2:47 left. Southeastern finished the game with six free throws in the final minute. Jermaine Griffin led Texas-Arlington (5-11, 1-3 Southland Conference) with 20 points; he also had 11 rebounds. Anthony Vereen, a Hammond native, scored 14 points and had a game-high 13 rebounds.
